  "timeframe": "5m",
  "market_context": "On ETH 5-minute, price delivers into a fair value gap and order block area. A continuation closure prints, but the entry candle has already taken out a prior short-term high, signaling potential exhaustion rather than clean continuation.",
  "key_observation": "When a continuation signal forms but the entry candle simultaneously sweeps a short-term high, the setup is compromised. Waiting one or two additional candles (and the next higher time frame wick) filters out failed continuations.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: Observed a quick move through the entry level producing what initially looked like a valid continuation closure.",
    "Step 2: Noted that the same move had taken out a short-term high, introducing the risk of a retracement rather than continuation.",
    "Step 3: Applied the fractal model rule of waiting for the higher time frame candle to print its wick before trading the next candle.",
    "Step 4: Confirmed price did not form a continuation out of the fair value gap area and instead fell lower, validating the decision to skip the trade.",
    "Step 5: After the new closure, identified a sweep of a low at a fair value gap point of interest, creating a new series of down-close candles to monitor.",
    "Step 6: Recognized the aggressive move forming a fresh continuation off the reversal and reframed the new setup as the tradeable continuation rather than the failed one."
  ],
  "outcome": null,
  "lessons": "If the entry candle takes out a high (or low) into your point of interest, give it another candle or wait for the higher time frame wick to form before entering. This filter avoids failed continuations and reframes the next valid setup.",
